# Changelog

All notable changes to the Mudae Harem Sorter will be documented in this file.

Changelog
[v1.3.0] - 2026-04-06
Major New Feature: Full Notes System

Added persistent per-character notes with a prominent green note pill on every card.
Quick Notes Setup: 8 reusable note slots accessible from the top "📝 Note" button.
Note editor modal with quick note buttons + custom note input.
Clear Note (per character) and Clear All Notes options.
Note Export: Generate ready-to-paste $n name$name$name$yournote strings for Mudae (automatically split to respect Discord’s character limit).

Improvements & Fixes

Top bar 🗑️ Clear button now fully resets everything (harem, locks, output, and quick note slots).
Sort by Note now properly respects locked characters (locked section stays at the top unchanged).
Added clear explanation in the Help modal about adding new characters to an existing sorted list.
Completely overhauled the Help modal with better organization, clearer sections, and improved readability.
Updated version display to v1.3.0 and added a "Thank you for using Mudae Harem Sorter!" message in the Help modal.

Technical

Notes are now saved persistently with the harem data.
Minor robustness improvements to note handling and clearing flows.

[v1.2.0] - 2026-04-06
Added

New import option: "Add new characters to bottom" – when a list already exists, you now get a choice between "Replace entire list" or "Add new characters to the bottom". Only new characters (deduplicated by name) are appended, preserving your current order, locks, and arrangement.
Auto-clear of the import textarea after successful import (both Replace and Add).
Toast notifications for clearer feedback on import actions.
Dedicated section in the Help modal explaining how to import new characters to an existing list.
Ctrl + Click on any card now copies the character name to clipboard.

Fixed

Help button now works correctly.
Clear button now fully clears the list and UI.
Jump to Bottom button now scrolls to the actual bottom of the grid (not the $sm output section).

Changed

Version bumped to 1.2.0.
Help modal updated with new import instructions.

[v1.1test] - 2026-04 (pre-1.2.0)
Added

Full save/load system (auto localStorage + manual JSON download/upload + paste import).
Slim top bar with uniform buttons.
Fixed sidebars at 775px offset from center.
Ctrl + Click to copy character name to clipboard.
Position counters on every card (x/y).
Note display as green pills under kakera.
Search bar that supports character and series search.
Navigation sidebar (To Top, End of Locked, To Bottom, Return to Last Position, Jump to Output).
Improved $sm command generation with proper $smpos chaining and per-box copy buttons.

Fixed

Series detection (DANMACHI special case and long titles).
Various layout and button alignment issues from earlier iterations.

[v1.0] - Initial Stable Release
Added

Core Mudae export parser ($mmak-i-s / $mmaki-s support).
Drag & drop grid with locked section pinning.
Per-card controls (↑ ↓ SERIES Lock/Unlock).
Sorting by Name, Series, Kakera (with reverse on second click).
Shuffle Unlocked.
$sm command generation with automatic splitting.
Help modal with full instructions.
Basic save system foundation.

---

**Thank you for using Mudae Harem Sorter!**
